---
title: "Ep 170: Zack Snyder's Justice League (2021) Recap &amp; Review"
publishDate: "2021-03-24"
category: "major-issues"
episodeNumber: 174
spotifyUrl: "https://comicbookclique.podbean.com/e/ep-170-zack-snyders-justice-league/"
---

The bell has been rung. The fight has been won. After four years of campaigns, hashtags, and reshoots, Zack Snyder's original vision for the Justice League is here, but is it an improvement on the original? Coming in just a bit over four hours of content, there is a lot to discuss when it comes to an unshackled Snyder in regards to the DCEU. What direction will DC go in now? Should Snyder get another bite of the proverbial apple? When will we #ReleaseTheHotDogCut? Some of those questions and more will be answered as we enter what could be our last time in the Snyderverse.

Suicide Prevention Hotline: 1-800-273-8255

